text.0: A Project Veritas video suggests that U.S. Postal Service employees backdated ballots in Michigan. The claim is unproven, but, even if true, no ballots in the state are accepted after Nov. 3, regardless of the postmark. https://t.co/6tlPsdpjmK #FactCHAT
text.1: Twitter has added warning labels to nine of President Trump’s post-election tweets, cautioning the messages “might be misleading.” They are misleading, and in some cases, false. We look at all nine. https://t.co/IrJPtEbVxc #FactCHAT
text.2: Facebook users are sharing a misleading meme that alleges a host of inaccuracies in Detroit’s voter rolls. But the claims stem from a 2019 lawsuit that was withdrawn after the group that filed it said the city had taken action on the issues.  #FactCHAT https://t.co/pyTJdRlWlt
text.3: The U.S. intelligence community had publicly identified three actors that it warned were trying to interfere in the 2020 presidential election: Russia, China and Iran — not “big media, big money and big tech,” as Trump falsely alleged yesterday. https://t.co/zG5BYlZyPf #FactCHAT
